{{Quote|And you thought swoop bike racing was a scary sport &mdash; these guys do this sort of thing for fun|[[Birdigan Nasalle]]|<ref name="The Free-Trader's Guide to Sevarcos">{{JournalCite|2|The Free-Trader's Guide to Sevarcos}}</ref>}}
The '''Festival of the High Winds''' was an annual event in [[Sevari]] culture, taking place at the late season equinox. [[Clan leader]]s, [[clan lord]]s and [[spice lord]]s and other clan representatives would attend ceremonies. Often [[Spice/Legends|spice]] merchants, [[Crime lord/Legends|crime lords]], slavers, [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperials]] and others with interests in spice trading would participate in the events.

The main events at the festival were the thrilling wind races, in which clans would race their [[wind rider]]s through nearby canyons at break neck speed in a tribute to their ancestors. The races were extremely dangerous, and their crews would use whatever means necessary to prevent the other parties from winning the race&mdash;including violence.

